-- ICE Exchange Raises Margins on Sugar Futures by 9.9% as of Close Nov. 12
-- B y   D e b a r a t i   R o y
-- 2010-11-12T21:18:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/ice-exchange-raises-margins-on-sugar-futures-by-9-9-as-of-close-nov-12.html
ICE Futures U.S. raised margins on
sugar futures by 9.9 percent effective as of the close of
trading today.  The margin requirement, or the amount of money traders must
keep on deposit, rose to $5,460 per speculative contract from
$4,970, the exchange said today in a statement posted on its
website. The amount on a contract for hedging rose to $3,900
from $3,550.  To contact the reporter on this story:
